Health Minister Carla Vizzotti and the brand-new Cabinet chief Juan Manzur this week announced new measures for what the latter said the government hoped is “the last stage of the pandemic.” Starting October 1, nobody is obliged to use a face-mask when outdoors, unless in a crowd, although their use remains obligatory while indoors. In addition: The Alberto Fernández administration also confirmed it would be opening up Argentina's frontiers, removing caps on arrivals and loosening rules for new arrivals: